==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gallicanism
<hw>Gal"li*can*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The principles,
tendencies, or action of those, within the Roman Catholic Church in
France, who (esp. in 1682) sought to restrict the papal authority in
that country and increase the power of the national church.</def>
<rj><au>Schaff-Herzog Encyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gallicism</ent>⟦br⟧
